Issue #5: curl|bash Remote Code Execution (CRITICAL SECURITY)
--------------------------------------------------------------
Priority: 🚨 CRITICAL
CVSS Score: 9.8
Location: roles/common/zFiles/twingate.yml:11
Impact: Full system compromise with root access
Estimated fix time: 30 minutes

Command being executed:
  shell: curl -s https://binaries.twingate.com/client/linux/install.sh | sudo bash

Attack Vectors:
- Man-in-the-Middle attacks
- DNS spoofing
- Compromised upstream server

Recommended Fix:
1. Download script to temporary file with get_url module
2. Verify checksum/signature
3. Review script contents
4. Execute with proper error handling

Issue #3: Hardcoded Username 'dgarner' (CRITICAL BREAKING)
-----------------------------------------------------------
Priority: 🚨 CRITICAL
Occurrences: 22 across 5 files
Impact: Breaks portability, prevents multi-user deployments
Estimated fix time: 2 hours

Files Affected:
- setup.yml (14 occurrences)
- power_management.yml (6 occurrences)
- touchpad_settings.yml (7 occurrences)
- n8n.yml (2 occurrences)
- docker.yml (1 occurrence)

Recommended Fix:
1. Add ansible_user_id variable to defaults/main.yml
2. Replace all hardcoded "dgarner" with {{ ansible_user_id }}
3. Add fallback: ansible_user_id | default(ansible_env.USER)

